	  <h2>Description of Course</h2>
	  <p>
	    Students will learn why machine learning is a
	    fundamentally different way of writing computer programs,
	    and why this approach is often a uniquely attractive way
	    of solving practical problems. Machine learning is all
	    about automatic ways for computers to find patterns in
	    datasets; students will learn both advantages and unique
	    risks that this approach offers. They will learn the
	    fundamental computational methods, algorithms, and
	    perspectives which underlie current machine learning
	    methods, and how to derive and implement many of them.
	    Students will learn the fundamentals of unsupervised and
	    supervised machine learning methods, the computational and
	    quality trade-offs between different methods, and how to
	    adapt existing methods to fit their own research needs.
	  </p>

